    <text id="A9805T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Brady writes to give Stuart advice about a pending bankruptcy case.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Hon Alex H H Stuart Staunton VA</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-06-16">June 16/67</date>
                        <name type="place">Philad<hi rend="super">a</hi></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Yours of the 13<hi rend="super">th</hi>is to hand, am Sorry You had the trouble
                    to copy the agreement, what I wanted was a copy of the paper I left with you in
                    pencil, extracts taken from the Ledger showing the alterations made therein;
                    which I should like to have at your earliest convenience.</p>
                <p>I think upon reflection that our best course will be to put him Bankruptcy My
                    council here Mr. Bullett will add a postscript to my <pb n="2"/>letter and I beg
                    you will consult with him in the matter.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Truly Yours</salute>
                    <signed>P Brady</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Please direct your letters to 228 Walnut Street.
                        <lb/>Dear Sir <lb/>I suggested to Mr. Brady that perhaps you would proceed
                        in Bankruptcy. This is however for you. If you think the the object he has
                        is to remove his property from the reach of his creditors I should think you
                        could do so. I only make the suggestion for your consideration. Yrs truly
                        <lb/>John C Bullitt</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
